    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-11-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-11-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="506"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d506">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Pruyn</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Seward</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 67.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States in Japan</hi>, <hi
                                rend="italic">Kanagawa</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-11-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 29, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to transmit enclosure No. 1,
                    copy of the letter of the minister of foreign affairs ratifying the convention
                    recently entered into with this government.</p>
                <p>I remain, very respectfully, your most obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>ROBT. H. PRUYN, <hi rend="italic">Minister Resident of the United States
                            in Japan.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary
                            of State, Washington.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
                <pb facs="0608" n="588" xml:id="pg_588"/>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">No. 1.</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <persName type="from">Japanese Ministers</persName> to <persName type="to"
                            >Mr. Pruyn</persName>
                    </head>
                    <p>We beg to communicate to you as follows:</p>
                    <p>In respect to the convention entered into by our vice-minister, Saka
                        Hida-no-kami, on the 22d ultimo, with you, at Kanagawa, we have to inform
                        you that our government has undertaken to give effect to the same; in token
                        of which we send this despatch.</p>
                    <p>In order to inform you of the above we send this communication.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <dateline rendition="#left">With respect and esteem, <date
                                calendar="japanese-nengō gregorian" when="1864-11-04">the 3d day of
                                the 10th month of 1st year Genji, (4th November,
                            1864</date>.)</dateline>
                        <lb/>
                        <signed>MIDSUMO IDSUMI-NO-KAMI.</signed>
                        <lb/>
                        <signed>ABE BUNGO-NO-KAMI.</signed>
                    </closer>
                    <postscript>
                        <p>His Excellency <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert H. Pruyn</hi>, <hi
                                rend="italic">Minister Resident of the United States, &amp;c.,
                                &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                        </p>
                    </postscript>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
